than  15s).  The  results  indicate  (i)  the  importance  of verifying apnoeic
episodes;  (ii)  the  value  of  24-h compressed recordings for identifying and
timing  the sleep cycles and their possible relationships to breathing defects;
(iii)  the  need  for  improved instrumentation; (iv) the dangers of evaluating
clinical prognosis or research from parental diaries.
